&lt;p&gt;Staff Nurse Ward 32, Cardiology, Elective Procedures, Glenfield Hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are delighted to be able to offer a fantastic opportunity for a Staff Nurse to join the Ward 32 team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We require motivated, enthusiastic forward thinking people able to adapt to the changing needs in service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some cardiology experience or an interest in the speciality would be an advantage. Knowledge and understanding of both elective interventional cardiology and urgent admissions and pressures of managing admissions whilst prioritising workload would be advantageous.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a member of the Ward 32 team you will work closely with cardiology medical team, Cardiac Angiocatheter Suite and the Clinical Decisions Unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will provide a supported induction package which will include the opportunity to work in angio catheter suite and cardiology ward areas to gain insight into the wider RRCV CMG.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Ben Hyde Job title Matron Email address benjamin.hyde@uhl-tr.nhs.uk Telephone number 0116 2583176 Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ben Hyde, Katie Russell or Geraldine Holloway on 0116 2583176&lt;/p&gt;
